d. Deferred payment sale – is any kind of sales transaction in which the payment of sales 
consideration is deferred over a fixed credit term, in installments or on a lump sum basis;  
e. Fair value – The price that would be received to sell an asset or paid to transfer a liability in 
an orderly transaction between market participants at the measurement date; 
f. Hamish Jiddiyyah – is the amount deposited as a security against fulfillment of a contract, or 
promise, or completion of a transaction by one of the parties to other; 
g. Inventory – in relation to this standard is an asset held for sale in the ordinary course of 
business or in the process of production for such sale;

